------------------------------
## 1. DevOps & Continuous Deployment Lifecycle FAQs## 🔄 Code Integration & Automated Triggering

* Post-Merge Trigger: Merging a Pull Request (PR) into the Bitbucket release branch fires a release build.
* Compilation Tasks: The system compiles code, bakes a container image, and assigns a release tag.
* Initial Target Environment: The artifact is automatically deployed to the Dev namespace.
* Registry Staging: Newly generated image tags are published to the AWS ECR image registry.
* Feature Testing: Validate all functional changes directly on the Dev platform post-deployment.

## 🚀 Build Promotion & Environment Progression

* Definition of Promotion: Moving a verified application version step-by-step through higher infrastructure environments.
* Environment Pipeline: Code moves sequentially from Dev ➔ QA ➔ Staging ➔ Preprod.
* Risk Mitigation: Ensures identical, immutable image builds run across all cluster tiers.
* Access Rules: You must belong to the Keystone Bitbucket repo and possess authorization to log into Drone CI.
* Requesting Access: Submit a request ticket to the DevOps team to provision Drone CI promotion permissions.

## 📋 GitOps Manifest Management

* Storage Repository: All operational deployment manifests are managed within the nse-gitops repository.
* Internal Promotion Loop: Image promotion triggers when a PR is merged into the respective environment branch of the GitOps repo.
* Automated Updates: The Deployment Automation system updates the manifest files automatically.
* Target Changes: The system overwrites the image tag field block to reference the newly promoted build version.

## 🔍 Verification & Sync Monitoring

* ArgoCD Verification: Log into the ArgoCD controller dashboard to confirm successful deployment.
* Manifest Inspection: Select your cluster, drill down to the active deployment manifest, and verify the image field reflects the correct release tag.

------------------------------
## 2. One-Click Deployment Roadmap

* 📈 Enhanced Logging: Inject comprehensive telemetry logs to audit build promotion histories.
* 🔔 Automated Notifications: Alert teams immediately via ChatOps when a build completes or undergoes promotion.
* 💬 ChatOps Promotions: Enable engineers to trigger target environment promotions directly inside Microsoft Teams, Slack, or AIOps Chat interfaces.
* 🧩 Selective Component Promotion: Allow modular promotion of specific microservice components instead of building the full application stack.
* 📊 Metrics Dashboards: Deploy unified visual charts to audit environment health, sync status, and deployment trends.
* 🔏 Automated Agent Signing: Replace slow, manual release candidate signing loops with cryptographic automation prior to GA release dates.
* 🤖 Automated Agent Verification: Eradicate manual post-upgrade validation tasks by introducing automated validation checks inside build logs.

------------------------------
## 3. Code Quality Gates & Governance## Purpose & Definition

* Quality Mandate: Ensures all inbound code modifications satisfy core testing thresholds before branch merging or promotion.
* Code Coverage Definition: An automated engineering metric measuring the exact volume of code lines executed by test suites to highlight blind spots.

## Quality Gate Criteria
A pipeline build will reject promotion and fail the Quality Gate check if any of the following criteria are violated:

                  +-----------------------------------+

                  |   Inbound Pipeline Code Build     |
                  +-----------------+-----------------+

                                    |
                                    v
                  +-----------------+-----------------+
                  |      Quality Gate Evaluation      |
                  +-----------------+-----------------+

                                    |
            +-----------------------+-----------------------+
            |                       |                       |
     [ Minimum Coverage ]   [ Zero Critical Issues ]  [ No Code Smells ]

            |                       |                       |
            v                       v                       v
     Total Coverage          No new security flaws   No duplicated blocks
     must be >= X% (e.g. 80%) discovered on new code  allowed on new code

            |                       |                       |
            +-----------------------+-----------------------+

                                    |
                                    v
                  +-----------------+-----------------+
                  |  Pass: Safe to Merge & Promote    |
                  +-----------------------------------+


* Test Coverage Volume: Total coverage score across the codebase must be ≥ X% (e.g., 80%).
* Security Defect Boundaries: Zero new critical software issues or vulnerabilities discovered on incoming code blocks.
* Code Cleanliness: Zero duplicated code blocks or structural architectural code smells allowed on incoming changes.

